Cold showers usually trace back to a failed element, a bad thermocouple, or sediment in the tank. We diagnose before we recommend — a repair is often cheaper than a replacement, and we'll tell you when it isn't.

## Repairs we handle

- Pilot light and thermocouple failures
- Heating elements and thermostats
- Anode rod and sediment flushes
- Leaking tanks and pressure-relief valves

## Replacements done right

When it's time for a new unit, we'll size it to your household and walk you through tank vs. tankless — including the long-term cost difference, not just the sticker price.
